meanings.definition: Pressed or squeezed together too tightly.
meanings.sent1: The overcompressed box burst open under the weight of the books.
meanings.sent2: The overcompressed sponge couldn't absorb any more water.
meanings.sent3: The overcompressed balloon made a funny squeaking sound when squeezed.
meanings.sent4: The overcompressed clay cracked under the pressure of the sculptor's hands.
meanings.sent5: The overcompressed spring snapped back with a loud twang.

meanings.sent1: The overcompressed shirt was too tight to button up.
meanings.sent2: The overcompressed document was difficult to read due to the tiny font.
meanings.sent3: The overcompressed suitcase barely fit all the clothes for the trip.
meanings.sent4: The overcompressed music file lost its quality after being shrunk too much.
meanings.sent5: The overcompressed photo looked pixelated and blurry.

meanings.sent1: The overcompressed soil prevented the roots from growing deep.
meanings.sent2: The overcompressed garbage bag ripped open from the weight of the trash.
meanings.sent3: The overcompressed car trunk struggled to close with all the luggage inside.
meanings.sent4: The overcompressed crowd in the elevator made it hard to breathe.
meanings.sent5: The overcompressed folder was so full that it couldn't close properly.
